screen.screenDetails: A 96 condition 3D protein crystallization screen with original chemistry incorporating a range of low molecular weight ligands found ordered in more than 33,000 deposited structures. Developed and utilized in the world renowned Laboratory of Molecular Biology, Cambridge, UK. This unique screen aims to unlock novel chemical space previously inaccessible using conventional screens. 96 x 1 ml conditions in deep-well blocks. NOTE: Buffer Conditions may not be accurate, refer to LMB screen name LMB17 at http://www2.mrc-lmb.cam.ac.uk/screens.html
